    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-21T11:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-21T11:29:00-05:00" n="648"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d648">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.1237/2</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GWE1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-21T11:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 21, 1918, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 3.02 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Foreign Office informs me confidentially that Mexican Chargé d’Affaires has been
                    instructed by his Government to turn over Legation archives to Mexican Consul
                    General and return to Mexico.<note n="1" xml:id="d648fn1">According to telegram
                        from the Ambassador in Mexico, No. 1106, May 25 (File No. 701.1237/5), the
                        date of the instruction referred to was May 18.</note> Foreign Office does
                    not know whether this means breaking off diplomatic relations and has
                    telegraphed for further information to its representative in Mexico.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GWE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
